text:
Home / Brief / Minnesota exports sink to $5.2 billion in Q2 Minnesota exports sink to $5.2 billion in Q2 By: Karlee Weinmann August 28, 2015 3:03 pm 0 Minnesota businesses tallied $5.2 billion in agriculture, mining and manufactured exports in the second quarter, the stateâ€™s Department of Employment and Economic Development said Friday. The export total fell 3.8 percent from the same span a year ago, dragged down in part by a strong dollar. Overall, U.S. exports dropped 5.6 percent since the second quarter ...
